  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "_key": "intro",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Datum reference frames provide the foundation for all geometric tolerances in GD&T. Proper datum establishment ensures consistent interpretation of design intent, enables accurate measurement, and supports efficient manufacturing processes across all stakeholders."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "calloutBox",
      "_key": "datum-criticality",
      "type": "warning",
      "title": "Datum Critical Foundation",
      "content": "Incorrect datum reference frames can invalidate entire tolerance schemes and lead to assembly problems. Datum establishment must align with part function and manufacturing requirements."
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "_key": "section1",
      "style": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Datum Reference Frame Fundamentals"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "_key": "drf-definition",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "A datum reference frame (DRF) is a coordinate system established from real part features to serve as the origin for geometric tolerances. It provides a common reference for design, manufacturing, and inspection activities."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "technicalSpecs",
      "_key": "drf-components",
      "specs": [
        {
          "label": "Primary Datum",
          "value": "3 degrees of freedom",
          "unit": "constrains 3 rotations"
        },
        {
          "label": "Secondary Datum",
          "value": "2 degrees of freedom",
          "unit": "constrains 2 translations"
        },
        {
          "label": "Tertiary Datum",
          "value": "1 degree of freedom",
          "unit": "constrains 1 translation"
        },
        {
          "label": "Total Constraint",
          "value": "6 degrees of freedom",
          "unit": "fully constrained part"
        },
        {
          "label": "Axis Systems",
          "value": "Right-hand rule",
          "unit": "X-Y-Z coordinate system"
        }
      ]
    },
